OL,6,FLouis Doyle KC, for Mendy, said
OL,7,Fproceedings had been previously
OL,8,Fadjourned to allow for the sale of the
OL,9,Ffootballer's house near Macclesfield
OL,10,Fin Cheshire, and that he had now paid
OL,11,Fthe debt.
OL,13,FThe court heard the sum had not yet
OL,14,Freached HMRC. However, after receiving
OL,15,Fundertakings from lawyers, Chief
OL,16,FInsolvency and Companies Court Judge
OL,17,FNicholas Briggs dismissed the
OL,18,Fbankruptcy proceedings against Mr
OL,19,FMendy.
