OL,6,FJudge Briggs said: "In the
OL,7,Fcircumstances, there is nothing left
OL,8,Fin this petition. I shall accept the
OL,9,Fundertaking. I shall dismiss the
OL,10,Fpetition with costs."
OL,12,FIn response, Mr Doyle said: "That
OL,13,Forder marks the end of these
OL,14,Fproceedings."
OL,16,F"That's correct," Judge Briggs replied.
OL,18,FThe High Court in London was also told
OL,19,Fthat Mr Mendy, who now plays in France
OL,20,Ffor Lorient, owes less than #5,000 in
OL,21,Fcouncil tax to Cheshire East Council.
